http://www.usgs.gov/
The USGS is a federal science agency that provides impartial information on the health of our ecosystems and environment, the natural hazards that threaten us, the natural resources we rely on, the impacts of climate and land-use change, and the core science systems that help us provide timely, relevant, and useable information.

name: 2004-presidential-general-election-state-results-direct-download
notes: This data set portrays election results by State for the 2004 Presidential general election. It includes data for electoral votes and popular votes for the Democratic, Republican, and other political parties as well as the total popular vote.
